            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-04-06T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-04-06T18:00:00-05:00" n="34" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d34">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 EAC/4–545: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Acting <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-04-06T19:00:00-04:00">April 6, 1945—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2696. Reurtel 347 April 5, 8 P.M. Cornea 208. In order to expedite agreement on
                    control machinery for Austria you are authorized to consent to inclusion of the
                    word “reparation” in the title of the control division under reference. You
                    should make it clear that this Government is willing to agree in principle to
                    the payment of reparation by Austria on the understanding that such reparation
                    will not be exacted until the Moscow Reparation Commission shall have given
                    thorough consideration to the form and volume thereof.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
